oing to discriminate due to your fealty to special interest groups, you=E2=
=80=99re going to have to pay for it.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Gramm helped write the =
law that allowed for the creation of Citigroup and other Wall Street giants=
, and later was vice chairman of UBS AG=E2=80=99s investment bank. He prefe=
rs to use what he calls the language of the civil rights movement, comparin=
g an oil driller=E2=80=99s ability to borrow funds to the right to sit at s=
egregated lunch counters: =E2=80=9CDiscrimination is discrimination.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0I sometimes think that there is a  certain wishfulness in the assu=
med mechanism of ESG. ESG investors tend to actually care about climate cha=
nge. One thing that they want to do at their jobs is invest in businesses t=
hat they think are good and make life harder for companies that they think =
are destroying the earth. =E2=80=9C Fund Managers Live on Earth Too, and Se=
