ficient reason for a person to choose some investments and reject others.Bu=
t it is awkward to=C2=A0say that, because ESG investors are generally (1) f=
iduciaries for their clients and (2) also marketing their services to prosp=
ective clients. Clients would prefer to be told that ESG investing will mak=
e them money. So the ESG investors like to tell stories to the effect of=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9Cactivities that destroy the planet will have a lower long-term=
=C2=A0financial=C2=A0return, which is why we avoid them.=E2=80=9D And you c=
an certainly tell versions of that story, about the declining social accept=
