</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px=
 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You create a new cryptocurrency, =
WashCoin.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You mint a=C2=A0trillion=
 WashCoins and put them in your crypto wallet along with $2 of Ethereum.</l=
i>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">How much are your trillion WashCoins=
 worth? I mean, zero dollars, right?</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px=
;">You open another crypto wallet and put another=C2=A0$1 worth of Ethereum=
 in it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You send the $1 of ETH fro=
m the second wallet to the first in exchange for one WashCoin.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The next day, you send $2 of ETH from your fir=
st wallet back to the second in exchange for that one WashCoin.</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Now the trading price of a WashCoin is $2, so=
 its total market capitalization is $2 trillion, up 100% in the last 24 hou=
rs.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You still own 100% of the Wash=
Coins and nobody has paid you anything for them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">But, now that the market cap is $2 trillion and soaring, som=
ebody=C2=A0<em>might</em>.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is this le=
gal? In the <em>stock market</em>, no, of course not; it is =E2=80=9Cwash t=
rading.=E2=80=9D Is it legal in the crypto market? I dunno man, it=E2=80=99=
s crypto. Does this describe all of crypto? No, of course not, Bitcoin trad=
ing is pretty much all independent economic activity and very little wash t=
rading at all. Does it describe =E2=80=A6=C2=A0a certain amount =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0of crypto? Yes, absolutely. If you see that a ridiculous non-fungible=
